<li id="c71">
  <div class="cx" id="cx49452473">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">The problem is the energy required, not the spin</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1188570/49452473#c71?mode=alone;showrate=1#c71">1+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:224370">Sneelock</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>You don't have to hit the same spot. You don't have to attach anything. &nbsp;For example, nuclear weapons are like hand grenades: close counts. F still equals ma. &nbsp;Laser beams don't have to hit the same spot to push the orbit away from the earth. They simply need to add momentum in the same direction.</p>
<p>The problem with any solution is that large amounts of energy are required to change the momentum of a large object moving at a high speed.</p>

