  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Follow the links and let the big brains that spend their life's work on this stuff explain how a ton or two of spacecraft with ion drives is all that's needed to do the trick. BTW, I work with satellites and I assure you a payload of a couple tons is routinely lifted. Even using very light materials. NASA should be upping the ante shortly with a heavy lifter rocket now in development.</p>
